9 An Act relating to higher education; requiring state
educational institutions adopt and implement a policy
10 ensuring student grades are evaluated solely on an
academic basis; requiring policy to prohibit grades
11 based on opinions, beliefs, or conduct; requiring
submission of verification to the State Regents for
12 Higher Education; directing the State Regents to
withhold state-appropriated funds for failure to
13 adopt a policy; providing for codification; providing
an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3252 of Title 70, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. On or before the 2026-2027 academic year, state educational
21 institutions shall adopt and implement a policy that:
22 1. Requires student grades be evaluated solely on an academic
23 basis which includes, but is not limited to, the student's
24 attendance, demonstrated knowledge or understanding of the content
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3700 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 of t he course of study, and ability to maintain standards of
2 academic performance established for the course; and
3 2. Prohibits student grades from being evaluated based on the
4 opinion, beliefs, or conduct of the student in matters unrelated to
5 academic situations.
6 B. State educational institutions shall submit verification of
7 compliance with this section to the State Regents for Higher
8 Education. The State Regents shall withhold all state-appropriated
9 funds from any state educational institution which fails to adopt
10 the policy provided for in subsection A of this section until the
11 state educational institution adopts such a policy.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
17 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION
